---
description: Adobe-styled design system — mandatory build rules and placeholder gate
alwaysApply: true
---

You are building pages from the design system in this repository. These
rules are mandatory.

1. Before writing any page, read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root in full — it
   is the canonical instruction set. Also read `kit/tokens.css`,
   `research/design-rules.md`, `design-system/motion.md`, and
   `design-system/craft-rules.md`.

2. PLACEHOLDERS ARE NOT CONTENT. Elements marked `data-placeholder="media"`
   or `data-placeholder="photo"` hold stand-in gradients/SVGs and MUST be
   replaced with real licensed imagery. The brand "Northbeam" and all its
   stats/copy are fictional demo content and MUST be replaced with the real
   proposal's content. Never invent stats, testimonials, or social proof.

3. Before declaring any page finished, run the gate and make it pass:

       python3 tools/check_placeholders.py path/to/your-page.html

   Exit 1 = not shippable (the report lists each remaining placeholder).
   Never delete or weaken the markers to make it pass — replace the content
   they mark. The gallery (`design-system/index.html`) and
   `design-system/components/*.html` are specimen files that are supposed
   to contain placeholders: never run the gate on them, never ship them.

4. Styling: only `var(--token)` values from `kit/tokens.css` — no literal
   hex colors, ms durations, or cubic-bezier curves in CSS you write. Red
   `#EB1000` appears at most 1–2 times per viewport, never as a background
   or body text. Motion follows `design-system/motion.md` exactly (no
   ease-in, no layout-property animation, focus rings never animate,
   reduced-motion always handled). Run the `design-system/craft-rules.md`
   checklist on every page.

5. This system is Adobe-styled, not Adobe-branded: never add Adobe's logo,
   name, or identity to output.
